{"id":481,"date":"2021-10-26T22:01:33","date_gmt":"2021-10-26T22:01:33","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/shichengzhang.web.illinois.edu\/?page_id=481"},"modified":"2021-10-28T01:06:08","modified_gmt":"2021-10-28T01:06:08","slug":"ac-octatonics","status":"publish","type":"page","link":"https:\/\/shichengzhang.web.illinois.edu\/ac-octatonics\/","title":{"rendered":"Algorithmic Composition- Octatonics"},"content":{"rendered":"\n<p class=\"has-medium-font-size\"><strong>Abstract:<\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Octatonics is an algorithmic composition utilizing C octatonic scale to create aleatoric music for the game BGM. It is logically easy to implement under the musx framework in python but with interesting sounding. <\/p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-medium-font-size\"><strong>Music:<\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"474\" height=\"106\" src=\"https:\/\/shichengzhang.web.illinois.edu\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/10\/octa_2.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-644\" srcset=\"https:\/\/shichengzhang.web.illinois.edu\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/10\/octa_2.png 474w, https:\/\/shichengzhang.web.illinois.edu\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/10\/octa_2-300x67.png 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 474px) 100vw, 474px\" \/><figcaption>Fig.1 C octatonic (0,1) scale<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-audio\"><audio controls src=\"https:\/\/shichengzhang.web.illinois.edu\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/10\/octa_1.mp3\"><\/audio><figcaption>C octatonic(0,1) music generation<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-audio\"><audio controls src=\"https:\/\/shichengzhang.web.illinois.edu\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/10\/octa_2.mp3\"><\/audio><figcaption>C octatonic(0,2) music generation<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-file\"><a href=\"https:\/\/shichengzhang.web.illinois.edu\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/10\/octa.mid\">octa_midi_example<\/a><a href=\"https:\/\/shichengzhang.web.illinois.edu\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/10\/octa.mid\" class=\"wp-block-file__button\" download>Download<\/a><\/div>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-medium-font-size\"><strong>Code: <\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<pre class=\"wp-block-code\"><code># Musx is an algorithmic compostion framework created by Professor Heinrick Taube at UIUC \r\n# Install musx package through pip install musx \r\n\r\n# Import info and some functions are omitted, if you need source code, please contact: sz18@illinois.edu, Benny Zhang\r\n\n# chorder\ndef get_chords_octa(bar):\n    octa_scale_1 = &#91;0,1,3,4,6,7,9,10,0,1,3,4,6,7,9,10]\n    octa_scale_2 = &#91;0,2,3,5,6,8,9,11,0,2,3,5,6,8,9,11]\n    chord_list = &#91;]\n    for i in range(20):\n        seed = choice(range(8))\n        new = &#91;octa_scale_1&#91;seed], octa_scale_1&#91;seed + choice(&#91;2,3])],\\\n             octa_scale_1&#91;seed + choice(&#91;4,5])], octa_scale_1&#91;seed + choice(&#91;6,7])]]\n        new = &#91;new&#91;0]-12] + new\n        chord_list.append(new)\n    return (chord_list, octa_scale_1)\n#====================================================\n\ndef middle_octa(q, chords, scales, keey):\n    tempoo = 5\n    cyc1 = cycle(rhythm(\"q q\", tempo=tempoo))\n    rhy1 = next(cyc1)\n    rhy1 = next(cyc1)\n    for chord in chords:\n        rhy1 = next(cyc1)\n        for k in chord:\n            note = MidiNote(time=q.now, dur=rhy1, amp=choice(&#91;0.1,0.15]), key=keey - 12 +k, chan=0)\n            q.out.addevent(note)\n        yield rhy1\ndef melo_octa(q, chords, scales, keey):\n    tempoo = 10\n    cyc1 = cycle(rhythm(\"q q. e\", tempo=tempoo))\n    rhy1 = next(cyc1)\n    rhy1 = next(cyc1)\n    tone = &#91;choice(scales) for i in range(40)]\n    for t in tone:\n        rhy1 = next(cyc1)\n        note = MidiNote(time=q.now, dur=rhy1, amp=choice(&#91;0.2,0.3]), key=keey +12 +t, chan=0)\n        q.out.addevent(note)\n        yield rhy1\n\ndef octa():\n    t0 = MidiSeq.metaseq(ins={0: AcousticGrandPiano, 1: Violin})\n    seq = MidiSeq()\n    seq_2 = MidiSeq()\n    queue = Scheduler(out=seq)\n    queue_2 = Scheduler(out=seq_2)\n    # now getting the list of the chord\n    bar = 32;temp = get_chords_octa(bar)\n    chords = temp&#91;0]; scales = temp&#91;1]; key = 60 + 12 -1\n    print(scales)\n    queue.compose(&#91;0, middle_octa(queue, chords, scales, key)])\n    queue_2.compose(&#91;0, melo_octa(queue_2, chords, scales, key)])\n    #queue.compose(melody(queue, chords, scales, key))\n    # print(\"yes\")\n    MidiFile(\"octa.mid\", &#91;t0,seq,seq_2]).write()  \n \nocta()<\/code><\/pre>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>Abstract: Octatonics is an algorithmic composition utilizing C octatonic scale to create aleatoric music for the game BGM. It is logically easy to implement under the musx framework in python but with interesting sounding. Music: Code:<\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":1,"featured_media":0,"parent":0,"menu_order":0,"comment_status":"closed","ping_status":"closed","template":"","meta":{"spay_email":"","footnotes":""},"class_list":["post-481","page","type-page","status-publish","hentry"],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/shichengzhang.web.illinois.edu\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/pages\/481","targetHints":{"allow":["GET"]}}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/shichengzhang.web.illinois.edu\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/pages"}],"about":[{"href":"https:\/\/shichengzhang.web.illinois.edu\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/types\/page"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/shichengzhang.web.illinois.edu\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/users\/1"}],"replies":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/shichengzhang.web.illinois.edu\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/comments?post=481"}],"version-history":[{"count":3,"href":"https:\/\/shichengzhang.web.illinois.edu\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/pages\/481\/revisions"}],"predecessor-version":[{"id":651,"href":"https:\/\/shichengzhang.web.illinois.edu\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/pages\/481\/revisions\/651"}],"wp:attachment":[{"href":"https:\/\/shichengzhang.web.illinois.edu\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/media?parent=481"}],"cu